sql:
SELECT p.player_name, t.team_name
FROM players p
INNER JOIN teams t ON p.team_id = t.team_id;

SELECT player_name, nationality
FROM players
WHERE player_id IN (SELECT player_id FROM player_awards);

external_knowledge:
- The metaphorical expression "most crowded arenas" refers to stadiums with the highest average attendance per match;
- "Drawing the largest crowds, like a beacon attracting moths to light" implies that these stadiums are attracting a significant number of spectators, similar to how a bright light attracts moths, indicating high popularity and appeal to fans;
- The ranking system is based on the descending order of average attendance figures, where the top-ranked stadium has the highest average attendance per match.

sql:
SELECT p.player_name
FROM players p
JOIN match_stats ms ON p.player_id = ms.player_id
WHERE ms.goals = (
    SELECT MAX(goals) FROM match_stats
);
